What Happens Here?
->External CSS says â†’ red
->Internal CSS says â†’ green
->Inline CSS says â†’ gray

Final Output Color â†’ gray
Because Inline has the highest priority.


Task Day 5

Learn About Flexbox




DAY 6 â€“ FLEXBOX 
What is Flexbox?
ðŸ“Œ Definition
-> Flexbox (Flexible Box Layout) is a CSS layout system
   used to arrange elements in rows or columns.
-> It makes alignment and spacing easier.


ðŸ”¹ Important Rules of Flexbox
1. Flexbox works on the parent element.
2. We apply: display: flex; to the parent.
3. By default, flex-direction is row.


Basic Flexbox Example (Column Layout)
Parent = div


Children = p tags


display: flex applied to div



<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Flexbox Example</title>

  <style>
    /* Styling child boxes */
    p {
      color: whitesmoke;
      background-color: black;
      height: 200px;
      width: 200px;
      font-size: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      border-radius: 16px;
    }

    /* Parent container */
    div {
      display: flex;

      /* Default is row */
      flex-direction: column;

      /* Align items vertically (cross-axis) */
      align-items: center;
    }

  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <div>
    <p>First</p>
    <p>Second</p>
    <p>Third</p>
    <p>Fourth</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>


